  "format": "Sean and Amanda are still buzzing over Parasite's Best Picture and Best Director sweep, then pick through a bloated, 14-musical-performance telecast, rank the night's presenters, and start guessing next year's field.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "Parasite Wins Best Picture",
      "note": "and Bong Joon Ho takes Best Director",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Parasite",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "South Korea had never had a film nominated for Best Foreign Language/International Feature before this, let alone Best Picture. The hosts call it the first genuine break from Oscar precedent they've seen in years."
        },
        {
          "title": "1917",
          "year": 2019,
          "note": "The guild-anointed frontrunner all season; the hosts had leaned on precedent all year and had no reason to think it would lose."
        },
        {
          "title": "Moonlight",
          "year": 2016,
          "note": "The last small, unlikely Best Picture winner, but its win was clouded by the envelope mix-up. Parasite got the clean victory lap Moonlight never had."
        }
      ]
    },
